---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout title="Umain Arena — free browser FPS sniper arena">
  <script type="application/ld+json" slot="head" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "VideoGame",
    "name": "Umain Arena",
    "url": "https://umain-arena.vercel.app/",
    "image": "https://umain-arena.vercel.app/og-image.png",
    "description": "Free browser FPS: a fast sniper arena pitting Designers vs Developers, with 8 original characters, bots, rounds and a scoreboard.",
    "genre": ["Shooter", "FPS", "Arcade"],
    "gamePlatform": ["Web Browser", "Desktop"],
    "applicationCategory": "Game",
    "playMode": "SinglePlayer",
    "inLanguage": "en",
    "isAccessibleForFree": true,
    "offers": { "@type": "Offer", "price": "0", "priceCurrency": "USD" },
    "author": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "Umain Arena contributors" }
  })} />
  <section style="text-align:center">
    <img src="/og-image.png" alt="Umain Arena — a browser FPS sniper arena, Designers vs Developers" style="width:100%;max-width:760px;border-radius:10px;border:1px solid #3a3325">
    <h1 style="margin-top:22px">A BROWSER SNIPER ARENA</h1>
    <p style="max-width:640px;margin:0 auto">Designers vs Developers in a fast, playful team shootout: cover to duck behind, open sightlines and a scrappy mid to fight over. 8 original characters, bots, rounds, headshots and Unreal Tournament-style multikills.</p>
    <p style="margin:26px 0"><a class="btn-play" style="font-size:22px;padding:16px 54px;border-radius:6px;text-decoration:none;display:inline-block" href="/">▶ PLAY NOW — FREE</a></p>
    <p style="font-size:13px">Runs in your desktop browser. No install, no signup.</p>
  </section>

  <h2>Frequently asked questions</h2>
  <details><summary><strong>What is Umain Arena?</strong></summary>
    <p>A free browser FPS: a sniper arena with two teams — Designers and Developers — plus 8 original characters, bots, a round system and a scoreboard.</p></details>
  <details><summary><strong>Do I need to install or pay for anything?</strong></summary>
    <p>No. The game is 100% free and runs right in your desktop browser (Chrome, Edge or Firefox), with no download or install.</p></details>
  <details><summary><strong>What are the teams and characters?</strong></summary>
    <p>Two teams: Designers and Developers, with 8 original characters split between them. All are fictional archetypes — no real people.</p></details>
  <details><summary><strong>Is this an official Valve or Counter-Strike game?</strong></summary>
    <p>No. It's an independent fan project, not affiliated with Valve. Counter-Strike is a trademark of Valve Corporation.</p></details>
  <details><summary><strong>Does the game take a side?</strong></summary>
    <p>No. It's just a fun, lighthearted matchup between Designers and Developers — no gore, no politics.</p></details>

  <h2>Open source</h2>
  <p>Open source under MIT (except the audio pack). Contributions welcome: <a href="https://github.com/jacksonfdam/umain-arena">github.com/jacksonfdam/umain-arena</a> — see <a href="https://github.com/jacksonfdam/umain-arena/blob/main/IDEAS.md">IDEAS.md</a> and <a href="https://github.com/jacksonfdam/umain-arena/blob/main/PROMPT.md">the prompt that generated the game</a>.</p>
  <p style="opacity:0.8;font-size:0.9em">Umain Arena is a rebrand based on <a href="https://github.com/rubenmarcus/csbrasil">CS BRASIL: Treta Suprema</a> by @rubenmarcus.</p>
</Layout>
